    <description>http-ping is a small, free, easy-to-use Windows command line utility that probes a given URL and displays relevant statistics. It is similar to the popular ping utility, but works over HTTP/S instead of ICMP, and with a URL instead of a computer name/IP address. http-ping supports IPv6 addresses.  For each request, http-ping displays:
	
	- The HTTP return code (and its brief textual description)
	- The number of bytes returned by the server (excluding headers)
	- The time taken to complete the request (i.e. round-trip time)
	
	</description>
